The paper deals with string matching algorithms, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of packed text and the word-RAM model suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also presents algorithms for approximate matching problems, which may fall under the categories of computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
